recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 404/93 of 13 February 1993 on the common organization of the market in bananas (1), as amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 3518/93 (2), and in particular Article 20 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1442/93 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1299/94 (4), laid down, in particular in Article 4 (2), the date by which the operators in question should submit to the competent authorities the total amount of  bananas marketed during the three-year period of reference for the purposes of determining reference quantities for each of them; whereas for administrative reasons it is advisable to extend this deadline;
Whereas so that operators can benefit from this extension, it is appropriate to allow for the implementation of this Regulation as from the date of its publication;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Bananas,
